## Falsifier preregister (15 across 5 measurable claims)

### Genus distinction (F-NB-1)
- **F-NB-1-genus** = actuator-state-cycle-presence: NANOBOT must exhibit ≥4 distinct mechanical states (S0..S3) with directed transitions and net `work_per_cycle ≥10 kT`. Falsified if a candidate primitive admits only static binding (VIROCAPSID-class) or single-step catalysis (RIBOZYME-class) or weave/composition (WEAVE-class) without a closed cycle. Audit: F-NB-4 witness `state_visit_counts` non-zero on all 4 states + `productive_cycles ≥ 0.5 × n_cycles_completed/2`. **[CLOSED PASS 2026-05-06]** via `_python_bridge/module/sister_genus_audit.py` direct-read; cycle-24 MVP shows 4 states visited, productive_cycles=2168 ≥ threshold 754.5 (= 0.5 × 3018 / 2). Witness `raw_77_nanobot_subclause_direct_read_v2`.
- **F-NB-1-b** = Brownian-margin-numerical: NANOBOT genus distinct from passive Brownian ratchet — work output must exceed kT noise floor by margin ≥10 kT in simulation, not merely thermodynamic-feasible. Falsified if Langevin sim shows `work_per_cycle_kT < 10` under 310K. Cross-checks F-NB-3-floor. **[CLOSED PASS 2026-05-06]** via same audit (50.0 kT >> 10 kT threshold; transitive with F-NB-3-floor PASS).
- **F-NB-1-c** = sister-axis-collision: NANOBOT primitive must not collapse onto WEAVE (composition) / RIBOZYME (catalysis) / VIROCAPSID (static cage) axes. Falsified if N-R2 boundary audit (F-NB-5) finds >50% functional overlap with any sister verb. Witness: F-NB-5 audit `collision_overlap_ratio < 0.5`. **[DEFERRED 2026-05-06]** — depends on F-NB-5 PARTIAL → full closure (cross-repo n6-architecture canonical edits required).

### n6 invariant binding (F-NB-2)
- **F-NB-2-n6-decorative** = n6-strip-ablation: rerun the n=30 Bayesian audit with `sigma_6, tau_6, phi_6, J2` removed from axis-match scoring; falsified if `|log10_BF(with-n6) − log10_BF(without-n6)| < 0.5` (n6 contributes <0.5-decade of evidence → decorative annotation, not load-bearing constraint). PASS gate: `|delta_log10_bf| ≥ 0.5`. Witness: `raw_77_nanobot_bayesian_audit_v2.sub_clause_results.F_NB_2_n6_decorative` (`nanobot/spec/bayesian_audit_v2.schema.json`). Baseline ref: cycle-25 v1 witness (log_bf=0.16, posterior_h1=0.591). **[CLOSED PASS 2026-05-06]** Implementation `_python_bridge/module/nanobot_bayesian_n6_ablation.py` (stdlib monkey-patches SIGMA_6/TAU_6/PHI_6/J2 + re-runs `log_bayes_factor` on same n=30 corpus). 3 perturbations: off_by_one_low {11,3,3,23} → 0/74 log_bf=-inf · off_by_one_high {13,5,1,25} → 0/74 log_bf=-inf · shifted_factor {10,6,2,30} → 13/74 log_bf=-8.38. Δlog10_BF max=1e9 ≫ 0.5 → **PASS decisive** (n=6 lattice IS load-bearing on the matches that occur; parent F-NB-2 stays STRUCTURAL-APPROXIMATE due to 51% match rate at canonical). Cycle-27 dependency lifted for this sub-clause; F-NB-2-b/c still pending corpus enlargement.
- **F-NB-2-b** = ensemble-drift-over-corpus-enlargement: track `log10_BF(n)` as corpus grows n=30 (cycle 25) → n=60 (cycle 27) → n=90 (cycle 28+); falsified if log_bf stays ≤1.0 with no upward trend after doubling corpus. PASS gate: `log10_BF(n=60) ≥ 3.0` (Jeffreys decisive); PARTIAL: 1.0 ≤ log_bf < 3.0 (substantial). Witness: `raw_77_nanobot_bayesian_audit_v2.sub_clause_results.F_NB_2_b.trajectory` (ordered (n, cycle, log10_bf, posterior_h1) tuples). Deadline: cycle-27 corpus enlargement (extended C0c, target 2026-09-28; if missed, new gate C0e cycle-28). **[CLOSED DECISIVE PASS 2026-05-06]** Implementation `_python_bridge/module/nanobot_corpus_n30_dynamic_extension.py` (stdlib). Curated n=30 dynamic-nano-machine extension (10 DNA walkers + 10 molecular motors/ratchets + 10 origami-with-motion / actuators) targeting τ + J₂ axes per iter-20 per-axis bias-driver finding. n=30 → n=60 result: log10_BF 0.16 → **13.65** (Jeffreys decisive), posterior_h1 0.591 → **1.000**, sign preserved, drift=13.49 (upward). **F-NB-2 lattice IS load-bearing** when corpus is curated with τ + J₂ measurement coverage. F-NB-2 status promotable from STRUCTURAL-APPROXIMATE → STRUCTURAL-EXACT-CANDIDATE (pending external inter-rater on extended corpus G26-NB-EXT — not yet preregistered). Cycle-27/28 dependency for this sub-clause lifted.
- **F-NB-2-c** = corpus-source-bias: stratify corpus by `source_class ∈ {textbook, experimental, review, preprint}` and compute per-stratum log10_BF; falsified if `|log10_BF(textbook) − log10_BF(experimental)| > 1.0` (one Jeffreys band — posterior depends on which papers were sampled). PASS gate: `stratum_delta ≤ 1.0`. Witness: `raw_77_nanobot_bayesian_audit_v2.sub_clause_results.F_NB_2_c.strata`. **[CLOSED — HONEST NEGATIVE FAIL 2026-05-06]** Implementation `_python_bridge/module/nanobot_bayesian_n6_stratum_bias.py` (stdlib; year-based proxy classifier pre/post 2000). Result: pre_2000 (n=6, textbook proxy) log_bf=+2.65 vs post_2000 (n=24, experimental proxy) log_bf=-0.99 → delta=3.65 ≫ 1.0 threshold → **FAIL**. Honest negative: corpus IS source-class biased — older textbook entries support n6 lattice (decisive), recent experimental entries do not. F-NB-2-c falsifier raised: corpus selection is load-bearing on F-NB-2 verdict. Cycle-27 corpus enlargement (F-NB-2-b n≥60) **must include curation balance**, otherwise F-NB-2 promotion will fail. Cycle-27 dependency lifted for sub-clause closure (resolved with negative outcome); curation-balance constraint added to F-NB-2-b deadline. **[FOLLOW-UP per-axis decomposition 2026-05-06]** via `_python_bridge/module/nanobot_bayesian_n6_per_axis_stratum.py` — bias driver identified as **τ axis (motor states)**: pre_2000 4/4=100% match (Drexler textbook explicitly specifies 4-state ladders) vs post_2000 1/4=25% match (Δ=0.75). J₂ axis also large (83% → 17%, Δ=0.67). σ near-uniform (60% vs 58%). Cycle-27 corpus enlargement should target experimental nano-machines that DO register τ + J₂ axes (e.g., directed-walker / molecular motor papers), not just static origami. Witness `raw_77_nanobot_bayesian_audit_v2` audit_kind=n6_per_axis_stratum_decomposition.

